        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Introducing Korus Framework]]></title>
            <link>https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/introducing-korus-framework</link>
            <guid>https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/introducing-korus-framework</guid>
            <pubDate>Mon, 01 Dec 2025 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[A new ultra-fast Java framework powered by build-time dependency injection and zero reflection.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Build-Time Dependency Injection for Ultra-Fast Java Applications</strong></p>
<p>Korus Framework is a modern Java framework designed around one core idea:</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI" id="move-everything-possible-to-compile-time"><strong>Move everything possible to compile time.</strong><a href="https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/introducing-korus-framework#move-everything-possible-to-compile-time" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to move-everything-possible-to-compile-time" title="Direct link to move-everything-possible-to-compile-time" translate="no">‚Äã</a></h3>
<p>Reflection, classpath scanning, proxies, and runtime bean creation all slow down traditional Java frameworks. Korus eliminates all of them by generating:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Dependency wiring</li>
<li class="">DI registries</li>
<li class="">Routing metadata</li>
<li class="">Bootstrapping code</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>during compilation</strong>, not at runtime.</p>
<p>The result:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong>120‚Äì250 ms startup time</strong></li>
<li class=""><strong>~50 MB memory footprint</strong></li>
<li class=""><strong>Zero reflection</strong></li>
<li class=""><strong>Deterministic, safe DI graph</strong></li>
<li class=""><strong>Lightweight Undertow runtime</strong></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI" id="why-i-built-korus">Why I Built Korus<a href="https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/introducing-korus-framework#why-i-built-korus" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Why I Built Korus" title="Direct link to Why I Built Korus" translate="no">‚Äã</a></h2>
<p>While working with Spring Boot and Micronaut, I noticed a common issue:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>Even build-time DI frameworks keep some runtime magic.</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Some still rely on reflection, some use proxies, some still scan packages.<br>
This inspired the architecture of Korus:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Pure annotation processing</li>
<li class="">Pure compile-time registry generation</li>
<li class="">No runtime analysis</li>
<li class="">No surprises</li>
</ul>
<p>Korus aims to bring:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">The <strong>developer experience of Spring</strong></li>
<li class="">The <strong>performance of Quarkus/Micronaut</strong></li>
<li class="">And a <strong>clean, minimal runtime</strong></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI" id="architecture-overview">Architecture Overview<a href="https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/introducing-korus-framework#architecture-overview" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Architecture Overview" title="Direct link to Architecture Overview" translate="no">‚Äã</a></h2>
<p>Korus consists of <strong>two independent modules</strong>:</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI" id="1-korus-processor-build-time-engine"><strong>1. Korus Processor (Build-Time Engine)</strong><a href="https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/introducing-korus-framework#1-korus-processor-build-time-engine" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 1-korus-processor-build-time-engine" title="Direct link to 1-korus-processor-build-time-engine" translate="no">‚Äã</a></h3>
<p>Responsible for:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Scanning source code</li>
<li class="">Building the DI graph</li>
<li class="">Performing Jandex indexing</li>
<li class="">Generating wiring and route registries</li>
<li class="">Auto-generating <code>KorusMain</code></li>
</ul>
